The paper deals with natural language processing and entity linking, which are core topics in the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of a graphical model and probabilistic approach suggests a focus on machine learning and probabilistic modeling, which are also relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the mention of a heavy-tailed distribution of entities suggests a potential connection to database systems (cs.DB) and data management.
